page.title: 10Woodlands Round Boynton
page.content: In our area we have got 11 small woods. One wood is called Foxcover. It is 100 metres by 600 metres. In Foxcover the trees are ash, sycamore, beech, chestnut, fir, elm, hawthorn and oak. Cottage Wood is 600 metres by 400 metres. The trees are spruce, ash, elm and pine. North Wood is 350 metres by 400 metres. In North Wood the trees are sycamore, ash, white beam, elm, judas tree, horse chestnut, alder and hazel. At Binsdale farm the farmer there has planted some new trees. Altogether there are 2 acres of land that are newly planted. In that land the trees are ash, white beam, cherry, hawthorn, holly, Scots pine and Guelder rose. Dicky Wood is 400 metres by 100 metres. The wood is a new plantation. Also at East Leys farm there is a new plantation.
